-- Mattingly Joins Gibson in Dodgers-Diamondbacks Brawl Suspensions
-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s
-- 2013-06-14T17:31:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-14/mattingly-joins-gibson-in-dodgers-diamondbacks-brawl-suspensions.html
Los Angeles Dodgers manager Don
Mattingly and Arizona Diamondbacks manager Kirk Gibson were
among eight suspended by Major League Baseball after a fight
between the teams June 11.  Also suspended were Arizona pitcher Ian Kennedy for 10
games and infielder Eric Hinske for five; Dodgers pitcher J.P.
Howell, infielder Skip Schumaker and hitting coach  Mark McGwire 
for two; and Dodgers pitcher Ronald Belisario for one.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eben Novy-Williams in New York at 
